Input: 15 messy employee records
Output: 8 cleaned records (7 rows removed due to invalid data)
Issues fixed:
Removed rows with missing or invalid emails (6 rows)
Removed row with missing name (1 row)
Normalized phone numbers to XXX-XXX-XXXX format
Standardized city names to title case
Converted state names/abbreviations to 2-letter codes
Normalized dates to YYYY-MM-DD format
Capitalized names properly


The main normalization file is employee_data_normalizer.py

It contains the EmployeeDataNormalizer class with all the cleaning logic:

Email validation
Phone number formatting
Name normalization
State/city standardization
Date formatting
Duplicate removal
Data validation